properties.title: Alpine Carpet & Upholstery Cleaning
properties.description: <p><strong>Alpine Carpet & Upholstery Cleaning</strong><br />601 North 700 East<br />Lehi, UT 84043<br />(801) 768-0862<br /><a href="http://ezlocal.com/ut/lehi/carpet-cleaning-service/30975">ezlocal.com/ut/lehi/carpet-cleaning-service/30975</a></p><div>When first starting out in the cleaning industry we were exposed to different cleaning methods and ideas from others in the industry. After very careful observation and research we determined for ourselves what type of cleaning services we wanted to offer our clients. We wanted to provide valuable services and maintain the highest customer satisfaction possible. Our goal when starting out was to maintain satisfaction with all our clients and keep them returning on a regular basis. We did not want to be known as a company that was content to have you as a one-time customer.<br /><br /> We pride ourselves in offering you the best and doing all we can to keep you happy with all we do. By taking the time and steps necessary to become certified by the cleaning industry and also maintain an ongoing commitment to stay well educated in all areas of services we offer.<br /><br />After 15+ years of being in the business we are proud to say we have achieved our goals and enjoy working for all our clients maintaining the confidence that is placed in us each time we're called and for doing the best job possible!!<br /><br />Carpet Cleaning:<br /><br />We use the hot water extraction method of cleaning, also known as steam cleaning, using truck-mounted equipment. Our carpet cleaning service begins with a carpet inspection that determines the carpet's condition, any spots that will need special treatment, fiber identification for proper pre-spray application, and to look for any possible repairs that may be needed. We then apply the proper pre-spray to all areas that will be cleaned. (using professional cleaning solutions only.) The pre-spray is agitated into the carpet in heavily solided areas. We extract the carpet using hot water and a neutral cleaning agent, unless the situation warrants otherwise. After the basic cleaning is completed a spot check and walk-through with the client is performed. Protector is applied, if requested, and then the carpet is groomed.<br />** Extra special care is taken when we clean your carpets by using corner guards to protect your walls, plastic or foam blocks put under your furniture, and fan placed for speed drying, in most cases.<br /><br />Upholstery Cleaning:<br /><br />We use the hot water extraction method of cleaning, also known as steam cleaning, using truck-mounted equipment. Our services begin with an inspection of the furniture to determine the fiber identification for the proper cleaning process. We will test for possible color bleeding, when necessary, at this time as well. we apply the proper professional pre-spray and agitate it. Special attention is given to the high use areas such as the head and arm rests. The extraction begins using a special upholstery cleaning tool that allows for an adjustable amount of moisture to be used. When the extraction is completed, a spot check is performed. Upon request protector is applied. A client inspection will be done as the final step.<br /><br />Duct Cleaning:<br /><br />This service begins by preparing the work area. vents are removed and a 2&quot; hose inserted to remove all large debris. A rotary brush is sent down next to clean the inside of the duct by brushing the interior walls and loosening the more stubborn debris. It is vacuumed out simultaneously. An anti-microbial is available. vents are replaced upon completion. Dryer vents are also cleanable, using the same method.<br /><br />Oriental And Area Rug Cleaning:<br /><br />This service begins with an inspection and fiber identification. The strictest attention is paid to the possibility of the rugs colors &quot;bleeding&quot;. The rug is then dry vacuumed on both sides. The proper professional pre-spray is applied and agitated in. Special attention is given to the fringe, both in pre-spraying and cleaning. Cleaning is done by using the truck -mounted hot water extraction method. protector is applied upon request. A client inspection is done as the last step.<br /><br />Carpet Repair:<br /><br />We offer minor carpet repair services such as carpet stretching, seam repairs, snag or unraveling repairs, small burn, or damage repairs. We also are able to do re-installation of carpet.<br /><br />Spot And Stain Removal:<br /><br />We offer specialized spot removal. In most cases we are able to remove, or make a noticeable improvement on spots such as rust, blood, mustard, ink, fingernail and shoe polish, paint, permanent marker, red dye, furniture dye, lipstick, wine, grape juice, tea, chocolate, grease and oilL, gum, wax, varnish, ketchup, crayons, urine, etc. Two of the major factors that contrIbute to our success, or failure, in removing spots and stains are the length of time the stain has been there and if it has been tampered with. Some attempts to remove stains without the proper chemicals, knowledge and training can actually &quot;set&quot; spots in and make them impossible to remove. To increase your chances of success your best bet is to call us @768-0862 or 571-8222. We may be able to help you be successful, on your own, at removing the spot or increase our chances at removing the spot if necessary.</div>

For more information or a free estimate call Applications Unlimited Inc. for your Commercial and Industrial needs.<br /><br />ABOUT SPRAY POLYURETHANE FOAM<br /><br />Spray Polyurethane Foam (SPF), a total building envelope, is a system of construction components which provide protection against movement of air, moisture and heat. SPF meets the insulation requirements for both new construction and improvements to existing structures.<br /><br />Spray Polyurethane Foam (SPF) eliminates drafts and increases comfort. SPF helps maintain a comfortable, constant temperature throughout the building. SPF assists in providing indoor air quality. SPF reduces moisture condensation within the building walls and roofs. SPF reduces heating and cooling costs dramatically, maintains its durable properties for lifetime of a building, and reduces costs by providing an air barrier, insulation and moisture barrier all in one product.<br /><br />Spray Polyurethane Foam (SPF) is a closed cell spray foam insulation, air barrier and sound deadener in one product. It is safe, eco-friendly and energy efficient. SPF can be applied over most roofing substrates and offers an option to either re-cover or repair existing roofs. SPF is used to insulate walls, ceilings, crawl spaces, barns and garages, as well as tanks, boilers and burners. SPF reduces costs for roof repairs or roof sealing, and improves work environment by reducing noise infiltration and improving climate control in offices.<br /><br />Spray Polyurethane Foam (SPF) can be applied to commercial, industrial and agricultural structures such as pole buildings, storage tanks, schools, hospitals and more. SPF is sprayed directly onto many substrates including block, brick, steel, wood and drywall. Depending on the type of foam applied, it will expand up to 100 times its original thickness, filling in all cracks and crevices while creating an air tight seal.</div>

I don't use coupons to lure you in, because you end up paying more and i won't sell you something you don't need! I use the Rotovac cleaner for the best results and professional cleaning products. I will get your carpets clean at an honest price!  No bait & switch prices, You will know the price before i start cleaning!  How often should you clean your carpets?  If you want to extend the life of your carpet, you need to clean it often.<br /><br /> A dirty carpet contains soil and other debris that will wear your carpet's fibers. Every time you walk on your dirty carpets, you are grinding the soil into the fibers, permanently damaging them. A cleaning will remove the soil and debris causing the damage. How often you clean your carpets depends on different factors. You must consider how many people are in the home, if you have kids, if you have pets and whether you have smokers in the house. If you have two adults, you should clean your carpets every six to twelve months, if they are smokers every four months. If you have kids and pets every four to six months. You must remember carpet is designed to hide soil and it can hold it's weight in dirt. If you are noticing soil and dark areas your carpet is very dirty, it needs cleaning immediately. The longer you wait, the more damage to your carpet.<br /><br />To help your carpet last longer I recommend carpet protector after your cleaning. This will help against spills and soils and prolong the life of your carpet. I use a teflon protector a very good quality product.</div>

properties.title: David James Homes
properties.description: <p><strong>David James Homes</strong><br />8512 Truvine Rd.<br />Glade Hill, VA 24092<br />(540) 563-5057<br /><a href="http://ezlocal.com/va/glade-hill/custom-home-builder/41953">ezlocal.com/va/glade-hill/custom-home-builder/41953</a></p><div>David James’ mission is to provide affordable custom housing for the average family. We do packages from $125,000 to $400,000 and our average selling price is $190,000.<br /><br />David James offers a warranty package second to none, guaranteeing the basement dry for 15 years, a 10 year structural warranty and, most importantly, a 5 year workmanship warranty. Our total commitment to customer service and satisfaction is the philosophy of every David James Homes associate before, during and after construction, earning David James the Summit Award in 2008. The Summit Award is given by Professional Warranty Corporation for only the highest level of customer satisfaction. We cultivate an environment that respects loyalty and dedication, which ensures that every employee is equally committed to the success of your project.<br /><br />Since 1995, David James has specialized in building highly customized homes at prices below what tract builders charge. Our concept is very unique to the southern VA market. Rather than pricing homes with allowances for all amenities, David James Homes has a complete showroom where customers can choose everything from flooring to roofing. Customers love the convenience and we are able to give a set price for the home rather than estimates. The concept also allows us to purchase in large volume, realizing substantial material savings that are passed on to the customer in lower prices.<br /><br />Since 2003 our company's sales have more than tripled and we have been named to the National Homebuilder's list of 50 fastest growing builders for the last two years in a row. David James Homes currently builds more than 80 custom homes a year within a 60-mile radius of Roanoke, VA and Lynchburg, VA. In January of 2008 David James expanded its operations into the Winchester, VA area and has several homes under construction there.<br /><br />At David James Homes, in all of our dealings with new customers and current homeowners, it becomes very clear that our one driving force, our ultimate goal, is not just building houses – it’s bringing families home.</div>

This studio was built because Davidjon found that what was missing in the fitness world was Intensity. He noticed that when people found a mode of exercise that worked for them personally, they stayed with it too long or would get complacent.  Changing the mode of exercise isn’t always the cure for this problem; the key can be Changing The Intensity! Consequently, GTI Fitness was born.<br /><br />That is what sets GTI Fitness apart from other places!  His cycle classes at GTI Fitness are consistently more intense than the ordinary classes offered at family fitness centers.  The multi-level coaching and caring allows for both a high intensity training as well as beginner teaching.  His hands on style, as he likes to say, will get nothing more out of you than everything! <br /><br />Johnny G Spinner Pros<br /><br />GTI Fitness and Davidjon offer you an indoor cycling experience that is second to none! The cycling studio is designed with top of the line Spinning Bikes, a customized computer to track your chest-pounding, calorie burning, muscle building workout – Also equipped with surround sound and dance floor lighting, which all comes together to give you the ride of your life! The GTI ride heightens the senses, energizes, invigorates and motivates you to push to levels you didn’t know you could achieve. Indoor cycling is as high-powered as any cardio class. In fact, a 50-minute ride burns an average of 500-800 calories.<br /><br />If you are new to the indoor cycling phenomenon, it is a superb, low-impact way to burn a boat-load of calories while listening to invigorating, energizing music and riding with like people in harmony. We welcome any and all types of riders from the &quot;never tried it&quot; to the &quot;I'd die without it&quot;.<br /><br />Training<br /><br />The personal training concept is one of functional training, meaning incorporating every day movement into the training exercises.  Davidjon uses incremental increases in difficulty for weight training, balance and unilateral as well as bilateral exercises.  He incorporates shorter rest intervals and multiple muscle recruitment to increase the metabolism and caloric consumption to build strength and muscle.<br />Longer rest intervals and less complex exercises can be employed as well.<br /><br />“WHATEVER YOUR SPORT OR GOALS – WE WILL CREATE A PATH TO YOUR SUCCESS”<br /><br /></div>

Efficient Laser Hair Removal was produced by Alexandrite and Diode lasers.  Dark skinned individuals could not use these lasers for effective hair removal because early generation lasers were unable to distinguish between skin pigment and hair follicles, which led to the burning of those with darker skin.  Today this has all changed.  The advent of the new laser line, the YAG, and the re-invention of the IPL system has afforded excellent results for individuals with dark skin and dark hair.<br /><br />Permanent Laser Hair Removal can be achieved by precisely following each treatment protocol recommended by your Laser Hair Removal Clinic.  Most Laser Hair Removal websites have not been updated with current information, therefore may not portray the care that needs to be taken in order to ensure effective results.  We have found some website information to be as much as seven years old.  This, quite frankly, is unacceptable.  It is with this in mind that the Laser Hair Removal information you find on this website will be up to date, accurate and informative.  It is provided to help guide you and to help you answer the most difficult laser hair removal questions in your specific city.</div>

Our goal, from start to finish, is to maintain professionalism which creates a pleasant experience for our customers, no matter the project size.<br /><br />MC Granite Countertops works with only the finest quality tools and materials. Our promise of quality is backed by our warranty on materials and workmanship.<br /><br />MC Granite Countertops is dedicated to furnishing the best customer service. We realize our customers are the foundation of our business and are proud to provide potential customers with referrals from previous customers.<br /><br />We work with the most technologically advanced template and fabrication machines in the industry to provide our customers with quality workmanship. This technology also allows for the &quot;greenest&quot; production facilities available in the industry.<br /><br />GRANITE CARE AND MAINTENANCE GUIDE<br /><br />Natural stone is very porous. The best way to prevent stains is to treat the surface with a protective sealer. The sealer fills in the pores and repels spills on the surface, allowing you time to completely wipe it away. MC Granite Countertops recommends that you use care and maintenance products from StoneTech™ Professional, a DuPont company, that are specially formulated to protect and enhance the beauty of your granite. Once the stone is sealed, clean up is usually easy. We also recommend that you use StoneTech™ Professional Revitalizer™ Cleaner & Protector for day to day/week to week use. Revitalizer™ cleans with a gentle, pH-neutral formula that removes soils while reinforcing the original protective seal to help prevent future staining. These products can be purchased through MC Granite Countertops.<br /><br />What are the DO's and DON'Ts of Granite?<br /><br />Although your new granite countertops are stain resistant, we DO recommend cleaning up spills immediately to minimize damage to your stone.<br />Although your new granite countertops can sustain heat up to 350 degrees, we DO recommend using trivets or mats under hot dishes and cookware.<br />Although your new granite countertops are scratch resistant, we DO recommend using place mats under china, ceramics, silver and other objects that can scratch your stone's surface.<br />DO clean surfaces regularly with StoneTech™ Professional Revitalizer™ Cleaner & Protector or a similar product which can be purchased at any local hardware store.<br />DON'T wait to clean up spills on stone.<br />DON'T use cleaners that contain acid such as bathroom cleaners, grout cleaners or tub cleaners.<br />DON'T use vinegar, bleach, ammonia or other general-purpose cleaners.<br />DON'T use abrasive cleaners such as dry cleansers or soft cleansers.<br />DON'T use alkaline cleaners not specifically formulated for stone.<br />DON'T use scouring powders and abrasives because they will scratch the surface.<br /></div>

properties.title: Prasino
properties.description: <p><strong>Prasino</strong><br />93 S. LaGrange Road<br />La Grange, IL 60525<br />(708) 469-7058<br /><a href="http://ezlocal.com/il/la-grange/health-food-restaurant/30069">ezlocal.com/il/la-grange/health-food-restaurant/30069</a></p><div>Prasino, (Greek word meaning 'green')<br /><br />A family owned eco-friendly restaurant in the Chicagoland area that will serve breakfast, lunch and dinner. The name of the restaurant is the Greek word for green which is at the heart of the restaurant's mission - to provide healthy food at an affordable price in a modern, environmentally conscious setting.<br /><br />Located  just 13 miles west of Chicago, in LaGrange,  Prasino will emphasize seasonal, local, and organic food prepared in a kitchen designed to reduce energy and water use, incorporate recycling and use eco-friendly cleaning products. The commitment to sustainability goes beyond the &quot;back of the house&quot; and is incorporated in Prasino's eco-chic design. The goal is to create a restaurant that minimizes its environmental footprint in a variety of ways. For instance, the light fixtures not only have dimmers but  were also made from products that usually end up in the trash - wine bottles and cardboard boxes. Wood rescued from the demolition of Sportsman's Park Race Track became the table tops and reclaimed oak planks salvaged from a barn were used for the floor. Even the restaurant's location near the commuter train line and bus line gives patrons the option of reducing their carbon footprint.<br /><br /> The Prasino philosophy of supporting local growers, artisanal food producers, and organic agriculture whenever possible reflects the values of its owners, the Maglaris family, who have been in the restaurant business for three generations and are very passionate about great tasting food.  The  family's appreciation for organic agriculture and artisanal food stems from the experience of  growing their own food in Greece as well as making honey, cheese, yogurt, olive oil and wine. The food they served in their restaurants however reflected more mainstream American tastes of the time with dishes like meatloaf or open faced turkey sandwich with gravy and served with soup, salad coffee and Jello or a scoop of ice cream. At home however, they held on to their culinary traditions eating dandelion greens, lamb, homemade Greek yogurt, and bacalao, all of which ironically are now part of the modern foodie lexicon.<br /><br /> Peggy Maglaris Kopley, Prasino's General Manager, still continues the traditions passed down from her grandparents of growing tomatoes and making yogurt. Like many well-read mothers today, she became more concerned about how food was grown and where it came from when she had her son Alex. As a result, she made changes in her personal life by purchasing more organic and whole food.  Without being conscious of it, she was adapting the diet of her grandparents. While she was able to control her food at home, she found herself making compromises when she was at away from home due to the limited options available so she and her family decided to do something about it.<br /><br />Prasino represents the evolution of the family-owned restaurant. It now blends together the culinary traditions that have been part of the family's private life with their professional life. Prasino also reflects a wider array of dietary options demanded by the public as well as greater environmental awareness.  The restaurant will offer vegetarian, vegan and gluten free items made into familiar menu items which include crepes, frittatas, homemade soups, paninis and flatbread pizzas. There will be a juice bar serving fresh juices, smoothies, organic coffee and tea  as well as a spirits menu highlighting organic cocktails.</div>

properties.title: Rapid Machine Co
properties.description: <p><strong>Rapid Machine Co</strong><br />1572 S Maple Ave Bld B<br />Cookeville, TN 38506<br />(931) 528-7975<br /><a href="http://ezlocal.com/tn/cookeville/machine-shop/40642">ezlocal.com/tn/cookeville/machine-shop/40642</a></p><div>In 2003 two second generation machinists made a decision that would change their lives. Myself Jerald Welch and good friend and long time co-worker Kelly Flannery with the help and support of our families set out to build small niche machine shop. First we focused on the Davenport screw machine and it's ability to produce very high quality complex parts at high speed. We felt that since much of the manufacturing base in the US was moving to Mexico and China that a small and intensely focused shop could thrive in this climate of downsizing and outsourcing. We are dedicated to our customers and there needs for small to medium sized runs with super quick turnaround with flawless quality. We found that there were purchasers that needed our specialized and almost dying skills for parts that just didn't make since to source to Mexico and China.<br />   In 2005 we saw the need to expand our precision short run capabilities even further. After a year long search we decided to purchase our first CNC lathe. A Ganesh 4 axis 32mm capacity hybrid Swiss lathe and auto bar loader. This machine expanded both our size and shortened our already short lead times. After a few months learning curve we found that we needed even more capabilities and one year later returned to Ganesh Machinery for their new CS32 7 axis twin spindle hybrid Swiss style lathe. This machine gave us even greater means to help our customers with problem parts like never before.<br />     Now with six Davenport multispindle screw machines our Ganesh CS32 and our full complement of tool room and Quality Control equipment we can solve our customers most challenging problems.<br />    We service such industries as Music, Computer, Automotive, Educational, Consumer Products, Logistical Support Companies, Food & Beverage among others.<br />    We have helped inventors develop ideas into working prototypes and then production.<br />    We have developed new products for our customers from their ideas and brought them all the way from concept to finished assembly.<br />     Rapid Machine is poised and ready to help our customers reach their goals while building a relationship of trust and confidence that their needs will always be met and exceeded in turnaround time, quality and price. </div>

properties.description: <p><strong>Richards & Sons Plumbing</strong><br />4005 Manzanita Ave Ste 6<br />Carmichael, CA 95608<br />(916) 878-0020<br /><a href="http://ezlocal.com/ca/carmichael/plumber/44204">ezlocal.com/ca/carmichael/plumber/44204</a></p><div>My sons and I have been in the commercial plumbing business in the Sacramento Valley of Northern California for more than 30 years. During that time span, we have seen hundreds, if not thousands, of serious problems with broken and/or clogged pipes. We found that traditional pipe repair methods just didn't cut the mustard due to the costs and inconveniences related to digging and pipe replacement.<br /><br />We knew there must be a better way than digging and discovered that the CIPP process has been the preferred method of pipe repair in Europe for over 35 years. Thus, we investigated the process thoroughly and purchased the equipment and went through the essential training so that we would be competent CIPP installers. <br /><br />We've been using CIPP for since 1998 and have a pretty impressive list of installations throughout the Western United States. We utilize only the latest equipment and technologies for our work.<br /><br />The beauty is that CIPP is so remarkable ... it can be used to repair most pipes ... without digging ... only one access point is required ...it's quick ... and while we're working business can go on as usual. We have a gallery of typical CIPP applications which range from residential to heavy industrial to oil refineries and even U.S. Navy ships.<br /><br />This Sacramento Area Sewer District serves more than one million people in the Sacramento region, including residential, commercial and industrial customers. We used CIPP to line 4-inch pipes ranging from 20 to 100 feet. The pipes were lined from cleanout to the street without digging and we were able to reinstate the laterals, too. CIPP is so versatile ... it is often used to line pipes of all sizes ... from one inch and up.<br /></div>

properties.title: The Beachcomber Rehabilitation Treatment Center
properties.description: <p><strong>The Beachcomber Rehabilitation Treatment Center</strong><br />4493 N Ocean Blvd (A1A)<br />Delray Beach, FL 33483<br />(561) 276-6226<br /><a href="http://ezlocal.com/fl/delray-beach/addiction-treatment-center/37171">ezlocal.com/fl/delray-beach/addiction-treatment-center/37171</a></p><div>Ours is a private Family Center for Alcoholism and Addiction Recovery on the Atlantic Ocean in Delray Beach, Florida. Here we treat alcoholism, substance and drug abuse, and chemical dependency in an intimate, limited environment of 16 residents. Our combination of advantages is unmatched in the nation.<br /><br />Our Vision<br /><br />Combining the structure and discipline of an intense therapeutic program with the resocialization and experience of sober fun.<br /><br />Admission to The Beachcomber treatment center is based on several key requirements. Primary among these is the necessity for new residents to attend groups and be alert to information under discussion. Consequently, there must be sufficient sober time to understand and participate in our program. Some who seek admission must first attend &quot;detoxification&quot; at a medical facility. Our experience over decades in South Florida has uniquely qualified our administrators in making referrals to such services. If it is determined that detox is necessary we are prepared to help make those arrangements.<br /><br />Drug detox and alcohol detox are generally short term addiction treatment programs, usually lasting between three to ten days. The time spent in drug or alcohol detox is contingent upon the amount of drugs/alcohol being used, how long and any added medical or psychiatric symptoms.<br />Detox, short for detoxification, is only the first step in the addiction treatment process. Most people, due to the length and severity of use, develop a physical and psychological dependency on their drug of choice (including alcohol). When abruptly discontinued the individual may begin to experience withdrawal symptoms. These initial withdrawal symptoms may include sweats, cramping and anxiety or can be as medically complex as seizures or convulsions. The risks associated with suddenly discontinuing use are too great to be done without medical supervision.<br /><br />Drug or alcohol detox can be a challenging process and almost all treatment programs will ensure their program is designed to ensure safety and prepare their patients for further care. Substance abuse can cause profound changes in brain and body chemistry and one of the first priorities in recovery from addiction is to detoxify from toxic chemicals and their byproducts. While complete detoxification can take months or even years, licensed detox centers provide medical supervision during the first few hours or days of abstinence. Withdrawal can be physically overwhelming, or even dangerous.<br /><br />Many patients experience mild to moderate symptoms during withdrawal and can undergo detoxification without medications if they receive supportive care and monitoring. Inpatient medical detoxification services are appropriate for alcoholics at risk for serious complications of withdrawal or those with co-existing medical conditions.<br /><br />More recently, outpatient detoxification has been shown to be as effective as inpatient treatment and less costly for people with less severe alcoholism. To participate effectively in a treatment program it is agreed a detoxification process must have occurred. In many instances those being admitted have abstained from alcohol or drug abuse for a sufficient time to adjust to entry into the rehabilitation program. Consequently abstinence has served as detoxification to a &quot;workable&quot; degree and the resident who is admitted will be kept under close observation as he, or she enters the first stages in our program. However, in some situations detox may be necessary and this can be determined in the admission process by The Beachcomber personnel on duty.</div>

Victory offers a wide variety of full service machine and assembly work including specialized work not found at you run-of-the-mill engine shops.<br /><br />Victory Engines, formerly Myles Engineering, was founded in 1926 by Merridth Myles. Merridth built engines for, and raced in, the AAA sanctioning body as well as IMCA until 1941 when World War II was at its height abroad. At that time, the company switched from building race engines to manufacturing parts for the war effort. When the war ended and racing resumed, Myles Engineering converted back to building racing engines. In the years following the war Merridth brought his son, Gary, into the family business and together they continued to build engines. Upon Merridth's death in 1963, Gary took assumed the duties of running the business until his retirement in 1995. When Gary retired, he sold the business to longtime employee Ray Banyas. Ray continues to own and operate Myles Engineering, now called Victory Engines, with more than 30 years of continuous experience in the Victory shop.<br /><br />Over the years, Victory has served racers and enthusiasts ranging from the Stock Car, Super Modified and Sprint Car ranks to the quarter-mile drag racer, both local and national. Some of Victory's customers have included the likes of Doug Hevron, Bently Warren, Joe Gosek, Steve Groia and Dave Simard to name a few. The 'Wall of Fame' at Victory proudly displays photos from nearly all forms of motor racing. </div>
